<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="232" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,151,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Comment.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[332,521,151,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" refString="Tamanini, L. (1979) Eterotteri acquatici (Heteroptera: Gerromorpha, Nepomorpha). Consiglio Nazionale delle Ricerche, Verona, 106 pp." type="book" year="1979">Tamanini (1979)</bibRefCitation>
expressed his doubts about the validity of this species. However, the identity of this exceptional apterous species was confirmed recently based on newly collected material (
<bibRefCitation author="Cianferoni" box="[1240,1432,188,213]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" refString="Cianferoni, F. (2015) The forgotten Hebrid (Gerromorpha, Hebridae). In: Anonymus (Ed.), 7 th European Hemiptera Congress and 9 th International Workshop on Leafhoppers and Planthoppers of Economic Importance. Programme. Abstracts of Talks and Posters. Seggau Castle / Graz (Austria), July 19 th - 24 th, 2015. Okoteam - Institute for Animal Ecology and Landscape Planning, Graz, pp. 26." type="book chapter" year="2015">Cianferoni 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cianferoni" box="[151,401,223,248]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" refString="Cianferoni, F., Buzzetti, F. M. &amp; Zettel, H. (2016) The &quot; Italian hebrid &quot; Hebrus franzi (Wagner, 1957): disentangling a halfcentury dilemma (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Zootaxa, 4132 (1), 127 - 134. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4132.1.11" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cianferoni 
<emphasis box="[277,334,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,475,260,285]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Subgeneric placement.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[487,769,260,285]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" refString="Cianferoni, F., Buzzetti, F. M. &amp; Zettel, H. (2016) The &quot; Italian hebrid &quot; Hebrus franzi (Wagner, 1957): disentangling a halfcentury dilemma (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Zootaxa, 4132 (1), 127 - 134. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4132.1.11" type="journal article">
Cianferoni 
<emphasis box="[620,682,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the antenna of 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1253,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franzi">
<emphasis box="[1148,1253,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">H. franzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is tetramerous, without distinct membranous subdivision of antennal segment IV. This would exclude 
<taxonomicName box="[1115,1214,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franzi">
<emphasis box="[1115,1214,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">H. franzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the subgenera 
<taxonomicName box="[151,276,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrusella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,276,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Hebrusella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well 
<taxonomicName box="[374,457,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[374,457,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Hebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[465,526,333,356]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[698,871,332,357]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" refString="Poisson, R. (1944) Contribution a la connaissance des especes africaines du genre Hebrus Curtis 1833 [Hemiptera Gymnocerata] (Missions de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique orientale). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, Nouvelle Serie, 10 (3 - 4) [1943], 89 - 112." type="journal article" year="1944">Poisson (1944)</bibRefCitation>
. They commented that subgeneric division needs further study on a world-wide scale and phylogenetic context, and did not consider the subgeneric assignment of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franzi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">H. franzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We prefer to list this taxon as 
<taxonomicName box="[564,647,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,647,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Hebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[654,805,404,429]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">incertae sedis</taxonomicNameLabel>
without subgeneric placement.
</paragraph>
